# Summary
Amplitude Experiment's architecture supports fast, reliable experimentation through robust identity resolution, user metadata storage, and behavioral cohort access, utilizing Fastly CDN and AWS services (ALB, RDS, DynamoDB) for high availability, with implementation recommendations including local defaults and client-side caching to optimize performance.

